# Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge

We, as contributors and maintainers of **ReleasePilot**, pledge to make participation in this project a **harassment-free, respectful, and professional experience** for everyone, regardless of age, body size, visible or invisible disability, ethnicity, sex characteristics, gender identity and expression, level of experience, education, socio-economic status, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity and orientation.

We are committed to fostering an environment based on **mutual respect, collaboration, and technical excellence**.

---

## Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contribute to a positive environment include:

- Demonstrating empathy and kindness toward others
- Being respectful of differing viewpoints and experiences
- Giving and gracefully accepting constructive feedback
- Focusing on what is best for the project and the community
- Communicating clearly, professionally, and in good faith
- Valuing clarity, safety, and responsibility in technical discussions

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

- Harassment, discrimination, or personal attacks of any kind
- Trolling, insulting, or derogatory comments
- Publishing othersâ€™ private information without explicit permission
- Sustained disruptive behavior in discussions or reviews
- Aggressive or dismissive communication that undermines collaboration
- Any behavior that is inappropriate in a professional, technical environment

---

## Scope

This Code of Conduct applies within all project spaces, including but not limited to:

- GitHub repositories
- Issues and pull requests
- Code reviews
- Discussions
- Community channels related to the project

It also applies when an individual is officially representing the project or its community.

---

## Enforcement

Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying standards of acceptable behavior and are expected to take **appropriate and fair corrective action** in response to any behavior they deem inappropriate, threatening, offensive, or harmful.

Actions may include, but are not limited to:

- Warning the individual
- Temporary or permanent removal from project participation
- Rejection of contributions
- Reporting behavior to relevant platforms or authorities when necessary

Maintainers are not obligated to provide justification for enforcement decisions beyond what is required to maintain a healthy project environment.

---

## Reporting

If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior, please report it by contacting the project maintainer directly.

All reports will be reviewed promptly and treated with discretion and confidentiality.

---

## Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the **Contributor Covenant**, version 2.1, available at  
https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/1/code_of_conduct.html

---

## Final Note

ReleasePilot is designed to support **high-responsibility release workflows**.  
Professional conduct, technical rigor, and mutual respect are essential to maintaining trust in both the software and the community around it.
